org.uma.jmetal.measure.impl

Class SimplePullMeasure<Value>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.uma.jmetal.util.naming.impl.SimpleDescribedEntity
      • org.uma.jmetal.measure.impl.SimpleMeasure<Value>
        • org.uma.jmetal.measure.impl.SimplePullMeasure<Value>
  • Type Parameters:
    Value -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Measure<Value>, PullMeasure<Value>, DescribedEntity
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DurationMeasure, ListenerTimeMeasure

    public abstract class SimplePullMeasure<Value>
extends SimpleMeasure<Value>
implements PullMeasure<Value>
    SimplePullMeasure is a basic implementation of PullMeasure. As a PullMeasure, it is intended to be used by external entities through its PullMeasure.get() method. This method must be implemented by the algorithm to specify how the value can be retrieved.
    Author:
    Matthieu Vergne
